OL,3,CCumbrian MP calls for legislation to
OL,4,Cprevent children 'doom scrolling'
OL,6,FThe former Conservative government
OL,7,Fprovided guidance to schools in
OL,8,FEngland about the use of mobile phones
OL,9,Fduring the school day in February
OL,10,F2024, but it is currently not legally
OL,11,Fbinding.
OL,13,FMr MacAlister, who led an independent
OL,14,Freview into children's social care for
OL,15,Fthe former government, says the
OL,16,F"evidence is mounting" that children
OL,17,F"doom scrolling" for hours a day are
OL,18,Fhaving negative effects.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/12
